aAfGny alex/.rg/bin 5:0:a > 4:0:A,G,y > 3:0:n > 2:0:f
====== alex/.rg/bin 5:0:a,A,f,G,n,y

=====
rg
=====
collect all git repositories from cwd downtree
for all unclean, print summary + number of unclean, ex:
   f data/list 4:a360c63 Summer 2011 :5

=====
rg -v
=====
collect all git repositories from cwd downtree
for all repos, print summary + number of unclean, ex:
   f data/list 4:a360c63 Summer 2011 :5
   f foo/bar   6:e4b2f7a Check in    :0

=====
rg -c
=====
collect all git repositories from cwd downtree
find other connected media with similar relative structure
compare. Sync all clean ffwd.
If all have same linear history, sync all clean to the latest
if any unclean or behind, print combined ordered summary,
synch, print again, ex:
  w  z data/list 1:97e57c8:0 Spring 2009
   x   data/list 2:7ec2f74:0 Winter 2010
 f     data/list 4:a360c63:5 Summer 2011
    Y  data/list 5:9e2d557:7 Fall 2013
Synchronizing z,x < y. h is unclean, unchanged
 f     data/list 4:a360c63:5 Summer 2011
  wx z data/list 5:9e2d557:0 Fall 2013
    Y  data/list 5:9e2d557:7 Fall 2013

=====
rg -l
=====
list all known git repo status, for example:
 B      alex/data/list   4:a360c63: 0 Summer 2011
  f     alex/data/list   4:a360c63: 5 Summer 2011
   wx z alex/data/list   5:9e2d557: 0 Fall 2013
     Y  alex/data/list   5:9e2d557: 7 Fall 2013
 Bf x z alex/.rg/bin    27:4ef5cd5: 0 Super bug fix
 B  xY  alex/.rg/data  123:ef5cd52: 0 Blah blah
  f     alex/.rg/data  123:ef5cd52:10 Blah blah




=====
device is either a computer internal disk or external disk.

=====
label is either
   /.label (or if not available)
   machine domain name (or if external)
   the disk label

=====
abbrev is the first letter of label, case sensitive

=====
type repositories can be bare, working, or export
  bare has no working files and is always clean
  working has working files and might be unclean
  export contains files and a .git file but no repository,
    its .git file must contain the log summary
    when it was created (git log --oneline --graph)

=====
relative path - rg looks for directories under USERNAME, ex:
    /home/USERNAME
    /cygdrive/LABEL/Users/USERNAME
    /media/LABEL/USERNAME
  So, for example, the following are considered relative paths:
    /home/alex/bin/foo/bar
    /media/Baz/alex/bin/foo/bar

=====
.rg/data
  Store status of all repos in .rg/data by device name.
    $ head ${HOME}/.rg/data/*
    ==> .rg/data/fish <==
    alex/.rg/bin 27:4ef5cd5:0 Super bug fix
    alex/.rg/data 123:ef5cd52:10 Blah blah
    alex/bin/foo/bar 8:d5ec2f5:0 Blah blah
    alex/data/list 4:a360c63:5 Summer 2011
    ==> .rg/data/Baz <==
    alex/bin/foo/bar 8:d5ec2f5:0 Blah blah
    alex/data/list 4:a360c63:0 Summer 2011
  Even if Baz contains only bare repositories such as
  bar.git, it will be listed as just 'bar' without the
  '.git' suffix



=============

rg

INITIALIZE
global data directories
temp directories


SEARCH
10. run global: find / -name "*.git" 1> tmp 2> /dev/null

LABELING
20. discover the labels and names of each
/cygdrive/x/name, /home/name, /media/device/name, /mnt/device/name

ABSTRACT
30. order relative groups: for example
alex/foo/bar /home       ananda
alex/foo/bar /media/Baz  Baz
alex/foo/bar /cygdrive/c charlie
alex/foo/bar /mnt/Dave   Dave

STATUS
40. investigate status of each relative group
  c  alex/foo/bar 13:8a22d3d:7
a    alex/foo/bar 12:d8ad232:2
 B D alex/foo/bar 11:a3cda22:0

PRINT
50. print all in group if verbose or if any are different or unclean

SYNCHRONIZE
60. synchronize all cleans to latest
  c  alex/foo/bar 13:8a22d3d:7
 B D alex/foo/bar 13:8a22d3d:0
a    alex/foo/bar 12:d8ad232:2

UPDATE
70. update global data
  c     alex/foo/bar 13:8a22d3d:7
 B De G alex/foo/bar 13:8a22d3d:0
a       alex/foo/bar 12:d8ad232:2
     f  alex/foo/bar 12:d8ad232:0

LIST
80. print the whole global list

CLEANUP
90. remove temp files
